<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-05T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-05T13:36:00-05:00" n="157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23846: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Torreon</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Donaldson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Torreon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-05T12:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">May 5,
                                            1920—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received May 6—2:12
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Chinese Chamber of Commerce have requested me to represent Chinese
                                people in case of emergency. Awaiting instructions.</p>
                            <p>No change in the situation hereabouts. The Government has withdrawn
                                all of the military forces from Durango and sent them to Mexico
                                City.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Donald</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">son</hi>]</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>